Title Review: The government recommends that the people install this tracking software  but some of the bottom-level administrators of the sbs company have used their powers to force the captain to install it  and pressure individual captains to sign  and to show them every day? I didn't expect the world to develop in 2020. There is such a company that violates human rights and freedom! Is it a government request? It is simply slandering the government's human rights and moral bottom line! The installation is obviously voluntary. Some people in sbs take the opportunity to oppress the lower-level working captain  deliberately tarnishing the government's reputation. Why don't they just send a prisoner tracker to the unpleasant car captain? This is more dignified than oppressors turning their mobile phones into trackers. This is Singapore. High-tech management must also respect human rights and freedom  isn't it? Car captains take their body temperature every day at work  but there are countless people wearing masks incorrectly in society  and no one is forced to do surveillance. It is very caring  and it really makes people feel that living in Singapore is becoming less and less dignified. There is an old Chinese saying: Where there is oppression  there is resistance. Don't let modern society regress to a slave society without restraint  please respect people's human rights and freedom. Thank you!
content: The government recommends that the people install this tracking software  but some of the bottom level administrators of the sbs company have used their powers to force the captain to install it  and pressure individual captains to sign  and to show them every day  I didn t expect the world to develop in       There is such a company that violates human rights and freedom  Is it a government request  It is simply slandering the government s human rights and moral bottom line  The installation is obviously voluntary  Some people in sbs take the opportunity to oppress the lower level working captain  deliberately tarnishing the government s reputation  Why don t they just send a prisoner tracker to the unpleasant car captain  This is more dignified than oppressors turning their mobile phones into trackers  This is Singapore  High tech management must also respect human rights and freedom  isn t it  Car captains take their body temperature every day at work  but there are countless people wearing masks incorrectly in society  and no one is forced to do surveillance  It is very caring  and it really makes people feel that living in Singapore is becoming less and less dignified  There is an old Chinese saying  Where there is oppression  there is resistance  Don t let modern society regress to a slave society without restraint  please respect people s human rights and freedom  Thank you

Author: Hendra Harijanto
Review: When I woke up and pick up my phone from charging station early in the morning, this app already clocked in more than 25 exchanges. Author: PY Ho
Review: While the existence of this app got GovTech and SG to shout "first!" in the world, the implementation turns out to be relatively shoddy and hacky. The introduction of Apple & Google's Covid exposure APIs renders TraceTogether's methods obsolete, and unfortunately GovTech cannot trumpet "first!" anymore as Switzerland is the first one to adopt the new APIs i.e. more stable ways of contact tracing. Will revisit the app again if GovTech decides to eat humble pie and adopts the exposure API with better efficacy vis-a-vis end-user usability

Author: Josh
Review: Difficult to review since there's no real "using" of the app other than letting it run in background. Based on FAQs it does NOT seem to track your location, which is curious and seems like it would be helpful in tracing the flow of COVID. The app uses Bluetooth to communicate with other devices using the app so the govt can inform you if you came into close contact with someone who was infected or deemed to be a risk. Still an interesting and commendable use of technology to help control spread.

Author: Tracy SG
Review: For all those with error requests, just try again a couple of times and it will work. It's a new platform where many people are rapidly signing up so it's normal. For those who complain app isn't useful for showing covid case updates, GO TO MOH WEBSITE if you want that. App helps automate contact tracing + increases coverage area, allowing it to be MUCH more efficient esp when cases increase. For those with privacy questions, read about how it works in App > Help > Permissions and Privacy.
